### Test Authentication Debug - Use this in your HTTP client

### 0. VERIFY USER EMAIL (DEVELOPMENT ONLY)
POST http://127.0.0.1:5001/api/auth/verify-user-dev/azzeddine.siammed@gmail.com
Content-Type: application/json

### 1. LOGIN FIRST TO GET TOKEN
POST http://127.0.0.1:5001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "azzeddine.siammed@gmail.com",
  "password": "12345678"
}

### 2. USE TOKEN FROM LOGIN RESPONSE IN AUTHORIZATION HEADER
GET http://127.0.0.1:5001/api/users/117
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 3. TEST WITH DIFFERENT USER ID (use your actual user ID from login response)
GET http://127.0.0.1:5001/api/users/{{user_id}}
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE  
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. GET YOUR OWN PROFILE (/me endpoint)
GET http://127.0.0.1:5001/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

###################################################
# DEBUGGING CHECKLIST:
# 
# 0. ✅ Email verified (run step 0 first)
# 1. ✅ Login returns 200 with token
# 2. ✅ Token starts with "Bearer " in Authorization header
# 3. ✅ User ID exists in database
# 4. ✅ Token not expired (now 24 hours expiry)
# 5. ✅ CORS headers included
###################################################